{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|冉|alt1=冄|邑|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=city}}.

Originally the name of a state; later borrowed for a [[w:Demonstrative#Distal_and_proximal_demonstratives|distal demonstrative]].

Cognate with {{och-l|若|that|id=3}}, {{ltc-l|爾|that}} ({{zh-ref|Norman, 1988}}). Also compare ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}):
* {{cog|mkh-pro|*nɔʔ}} ~ {{m|mkh-pro|*nɔh||this}}, whence {{cog|km|នោះ||that}}, {{cog|vi|nọ||this}};
* {{cog|kjg|tr=naa|t=she}};
* {{cog|tai-pro|*najᶜ||this}}, whence {{cog|th|นี้||this}}, {{cog|za|neix||this}}.

